Note:
C++ Lexer - Tokenizer for the C++ programming language.

Produces a stream of single-lookahead tokens consumed by cpp_parser.runa. The
lexer recognises the full C++17 token set: preprocessor directives, distinct
keyword tokens (so the parser can branch on TOKEN_CLASS / TOKEN_NAMESPACE /
TOKEN_PUBLIC and friends rather than re-comparing keyword text), identifiers,
integer/float/char/string literals (including raw strings and user-defined
suffixes), and the complete C++ operator/punctuator set including the
multi-byte operators (::, ->, .*, ->*, <<=, >>=, <=>, ...).

Contract (mirrors the C frontend):
- create_cpp_lexer(source) -> lexer handle (owns its own state, 0 on OOM)
- next_token(lexer)        -> integer token TYPE; also caches the lexeme so
                              current_lexeme can re-read it without re-lexing
- current_lexeme(lexer)    -> borrowed pointer to the current token's lexeme
                              (a freshly allocated NUL-terminated copy owned by
                              the lexer, freed on the next next_token or destroy)
- destroy_cpp_lexer(lexer) -> frees all owned state

Forward-progress guarantee: every call to next_token advances the byte cursor
by at least one byte for any non-EOF input, and returns TOKEN_EOF terminally
once the cursor reaches end of source. Unknown bytes are consumed and reported
as TOKEN_ERROR (still advancing) so the parser's statement loops can never spin
on a non-advancing token.

Dependencies:
- compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa
- compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore

